    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="338"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d338">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894A.01/3–2649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Edgar</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-26">March 26,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received March 26—1:46 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>85. In local speech former Foreign Minister Wang Shih-chieh stated Taiwan is
                    “restored territory”, not “military occupation area”, <pb facs="0315" n="305"
                        xml:id="pg_305"/> and China has absolute sovereignty re foreign and domestic
                    matters. Shimonoseki treaty<note n="9" xml:id="d338fn9">Treaty of peace between
                        China and Japan, signed April 17, 1895, <ref target="frus1895p1#pg_200">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1895, pt. 1, p.
                        200</ref>.</note> was nullified by Chinese 1943 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >1949?</hi>] war declaration, Taiwan legally reverted to China then and was
                    physically reacquired from Japanese Army at war’s end. Warned against other
                    future direct or indirect attempts at imperialistic control.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking 78, repeated Department 85.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edgar</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
